  - Look visually for logos. If an image is a screenshot of a UI, an architecture diagram, or a random meme, classify it as "screenshot" or "unrelated".
  - If it is a clear logo, classify it "logo_primary". If a second image is provided that is clearly a dark-mode alternate of the logo, classify it "logo_dark_variant".
  - If you are not visually confident, set role "unclear" and confidence "low" rather than guessing — a human reviews every candidate before anything is committed.
  - Only set "target_path" for candidates classified as logo_primary or logo_dark_variant. Place it alongside the content file (same directory as target_path above), keeping the original file extension. (Hugo Page Bundle format).